The worker health server has no `'error'` event handler. If `listen()` fails (e.g., EADDRINUSE) or a runtime server error occurs, Node will emit an `error` event that can crash the process without a clear, consistent log/exit path. Add an `healthServer.on('error', ...)` handler that logs context and exits non-zero (so Railway restarts cleanly).
```suggestion

healthServer.on('error', (err: NodeJS.ErrnoException) => {
  console.error(
    `[worker] health server error instance=${instanceId} host=${HOST} port=${PORT} code=${err.code ?? 'unknown'} errno=${err.errno ?? 'unknown'} syscall=${err.syscall ?? 'unknown'}`,
    err,
  );
  process.exit(1);
});
```

